This was fun, but remember that lie detector tests are not admissable in court because they're only correct about 50% of the time. Measuring stress is not the same as measuring truth. The guys could certainly have been stressed out by some of those uncomfortable questions while still answering truthfully. Especially when Keith said, "Well, I learned something about myself," that's probably not a true. It's more likely that he was stressed by the question and the test gave a false positive. Similarly, Eugene might have been stressed out by the idea of the guys hugging him and been truthful when he said he didn't want a hug.


But yeah, it's a fun video.
